[Student "S"]
{Partner has at least opening hand and he has 4 \Ss. There is only one thing you need to know - how many Aces he has. You bid Blackwood 4NT and he responds 5\S. What is your next bid? 

The three Aces does it for you. You can count 7 \S tricks, 3 \H tricks, 2 \D tricks and 1 \C. That is 13 total so you go ahead and bid 7NT.}

